WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:05.206 --> 00:00:06.516
<i>Previously</i>
<i>on</i> The Spanish Princess...

2
00:00:06.540 --> 00:00:09.577
We should dissolve Princess Mary's
engagement to Charles

3
00:00:09.610 --> 00:00:11.112
<i>and instead match her
with King Louis.</i>

4
00:00:11.145 --> 00:00:13.481
Wolsey's counsel is against me.
and you are allowing it.

5
00:00:13.514 --> 00:00:14.782
You don't give me what I need.

6
00:00:15.015 --> 00:00:17.551
I stand here with a void
in the middle of my body.

7
00:00:17.585 --> 00:00:18.695
<i>and you think God
is punishing me.</i>

8
00:00:18.719 --> 00:00:20.154
<i>but I have done nothing wrong.</i>

9
00:00:20.187 --> 00:00:22.790
Your Grace. my daughter
wishes to marry.

10
00:00:23.023 --> 00:00:24.735
Young Henry Stafford.
he'll have her.

11
00:00:24.759 --> 00:00:26.660
And might I suggest
William Compton for you?

12
00:00:26.694 --> 00:00:28.229
Your Groom of the Stool?

13
00:00:28.262 --> 00:00:31.198
My brother Albany
must return from France.

14
00:00:31.232 --> 00:00:33.734
He's next in line
to the regency.

15
00:00:33.768 --> 00:00:35.245
As long as I do not marry.
I will be regent

16
00:00:35.269 --> 00:00:36.771
<i>until Jamie comes of age.</i>

17
00:00:36.804 --> 00:00:39.373
You are the greatest queen
Scotland's ever known.

18
00:00:39.407 --> 00:00:41.108
A Scot in France.

19
00:00:41.142 --> 00:00:42.619
Would you rather
I was back in Edinburgh.

20
00:00:42.643 --> 00:00:44.311
taking the regency
from your sister?

21
00:00:44.345 --> 00:00:45.756
Do you think we can
recover from this?

22
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:47.281
I want to.

23
00:00:47.314 --> 00:00:48.558
<i>I want it to be
as it was before.</i>

24
00:00:48.582 --> 00:00:51.185
<i>We are strong. Archbishop.</i>

25
00:00:51.218 --> 00:00:52.586
and none shall come between us.

26
00:00:54.000 --> 00:01:00.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

27
00:01:44.839 --> 00:01:47.274
The young men
of the court are impudent.

28
00:01:47.308 --> 00:01:49.376
Their eyes are ever on my bosom.

29
00:01:49.410 --> 00:01:51.445
Even during chapel.

30
00:01:51.479 --> 00:01:52.756
Sounds like you enjoy it. Anne.

31
00:01:52.780 --> 00:01:54.257
Of course. I do not blame them.

32
00:01:54.281 --> 00:01:56.116
But my husband is aggrieved.

33
00:01:56.150 --> 00:01:57.885
Anne.

34
00:01:58.118 --> 00:01:59.753
The child makes me nauseous.

35
00:01:59.787 --> 00:02:01.822
Please fetch some lavender
from the garden.

36
00:02:01.856 --> 00:02:04.825
Oh. uh...
yes. of course. Your Grace.

37
00:02:09.630 --> 00:02:11.308
Let us pray she catches the eye

38
00:02:11.332 --> 00:02:14.635
of one of her so-called
admirers and they waylay her.

39
00:02:14.668 --> 00:02:16.904
I think that they
are only in her mind.

40
00:02:17.137 --> 00:02:18.772
To salve her pain
that her husband

41
00:02:18.806 --> 00:02:20.140
will not attend her bed.

42
00:02:20.174 --> 00:02:22.409
Any other woman but not hers.

43
00:02:22.443 --> 00:02:24.445
She is not blessed
with happiness

44
00:02:24.478 --> 00:02:26.280
in marriage as we are.

45
00:02:27.848 --> 00:02:29.583
We must be patient
with her. then.

46
00:02:32.887 --> 00:02:34.822
I will take some air.

47
00:02:36.590 --> 00:02:39.260
Your Grace.

48
00:02:41.662 --> 00:02:43.497
Catherine.

49
00:02:43.531 --> 00:02:45.533
How is my magnificent son
and heir?

50
00:02:45.566 --> 00:02:46.643
Already looking forward

51
00:02:46.667 --> 00:02:47.935
to his first ale. I'd wager.

52
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:49.937
Can he throw a punch in there?

53
00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:52.806
He tells me he would have
air and exercise.

54
00:02:54.375 --> 00:02:55.852
But. Catherine.
you know you must rest.

55
00:02:55.876 --> 00:02:58.679
And sport.
He is his father's son.

56
00:02:58.712 --> 00:03:00.414
A king in the making.

57
00:03:01.549 --> 00:03:03.817
It seems he has
his mother's will.

58
00:03:10.491 --> 00:03:14.862
Ah. there's Charlie
with his bride-to-be.

59
00:03:14.895 --> 00:03:16.497
the radiant Lady Elizabeth.

60
00:03:16.530 --> 00:03:20.234
I believe we now address
this fellow as Viscount Lisle.

61
00:03:20.267 --> 00:03:22.703
Ah. that's right. Viscount. yes.

62
00:03:22.736 --> 00:03:25.372
The first of many gifts I'm
sure my encroaching marriage

63
00:03:25.406 --> 00:03:26.774
will bestow upon me. Your Grace.

64
00:03:28.342 --> 00:03:29.677
Uh. perhaps you will excuse us.

65
00:03:29.710 --> 00:03:31.579
Elizabeth wishes to see
the blasted yew tree

66
00:03:31.612 --> 00:03:33.614
in the grounds.

67
00:03:40.788 --> 00:03:42.923
What news?

68
00:03:42.957 --> 00:03:45.292
Uh...

69
00:03:45.326 --> 00:03:48.295
Wolsey asked if I'd consider
making him chancellor.

70
00:03:50.264 --> 00:03:52.933
He has just
been made archbishop.

71
00:03:52.967 --> 00:03:54.802
I do not think it
such a bad idea.

72
00:03:54.835 --> 00:03:57.571
It is a terrible idea.

73
00:03:57.605 --> 00:04:00.474
Lord chancellor is second
in power only to you.

74
00:04:00.507 --> 00:04:03.711
and Wolsey is already
high above his station.

75
00:04:03.744 --> 00:04:06.246
Would he have a title from you
every half year?

76
00:04:06.280 --> 00:04:09.583
I fought nine years
to be your queen.

77
00:04:09.617 --> 00:04:12.753
You fought. or was it I
who fought for you?

78
00:04:14.254 --> 00:04:16.290
It was you. of course.

79
00:04:17.391 --> 00:04:19.693
But I always wanted you.

80
00:04:19.727 --> 00:04:21.395
What woman wouldn't?

81
00:04:23.897 --> 00:04:26.367
<i>And I will want you</i>

82
00:04:26.400 --> 00:04:29.470
till the sun goes down
o'er all of time.

83
00:04:30.671 --> 00:04:34.508
Until that day.
will you be mine?

84
00:04:41.582 --> 00:04:43.984
You are a beautiful poet.

85
00:04:44.018 --> 00:04:45.753
It's easy with such a muse.

86
00:04:47.287 --> 00:04:48.598
Oh. I want to shout it
from the Highlands.

87
00:04:48.622 --> 00:04:50.424
Margaret Tudor is mine.

88
00:04:50.457 --> 00:04:51.992
and nothing will come
between us.

89
00:04:52.026 --> 00:04:54.695
It cannot. I forbid it.

90
00:04:54.728 --> 00:04:57.564
And I am queen.

91
00:04:57.598 --> 00:05:00.000
Or regent. at least.

92
00:05:01.001 --> 00:05:02.870
Tell me about her...

93
00:05:02.903 --> 00:05:04.605
your muse.

94
00:05:04.638 --> 00:05:06.707
I used to hear tales
of her as a girl.

95
00:05:06.740 --> 00:05:08.776
- Mm. virtuous.
- Hmm.

96
00:05:08.809 --> 00:05:10.377
Thoughtful.

97
00:05:10.411 --> 00:05:11.512
Devout.

98
00:05:11.545 --> 00:05:13.781
Headstrong. stormy. wild.

99
00:05:15.516 --> 00:05:17.351
And now?

100
00:05:17.384 --> 00:05:18.952
How do you find her?

101
00:05:18.986 --> 00:05:22.856
I find that she is a queen
not merely in title...

102
00:05:22.890 --> 00:05:25.459
but in temperament also.

103
00:05:30.798 --> 00:05:31.865
He is here.

104
00:05:31.899 --> 00:05:34.101
- So it's true.
- What do you want?

105
00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:36.670
- Get out!
- You. cur!

106
00:05:36.704 --> 00:05:38.472
You have compromised the queen!

107
00:05:38.505 --> 00:05:39.673
He has not!

108
00:05:39.707 --> 00:05:41.108
The earl of Angus is my...

109
00:05:43.410 --> 00:05:47.081
He has robbed
the dowager queen of her honor!

110
00:05:47.114 --> 00:05:49.083
Forced her. filthy dog!

111
00:05:49.116 --> 00:05:50.517
He did not force me!

112
00:05:50.551 --> 00:05:52.419
- We are married!
- What?

113
00:05:52.453 --> 00:05:54.822
By Bishop McElroy
at South Queensferry Kirk.

114
00:05:54.855 --> 00:05:56.356
Last Saturday.

115
00:05:56.390 --> 00:05:57.934
You can ask him if you
will not take my word for it.

116
00:05:57.958 --> 00:05:59.626
No. this cannot be true.

117
00:05:59.660 --> 00:06:01.929
So unless you want
to be hanged for treason.

118
00:06:01.962 --> 00:06:04.364
release my husband now!

119
00:06:07.101 --> 00:06:08.368
Away with you.

120
00:06:11.405 --> 00:06:15.876
If this is true. then you have
betrayed your country. madam.

121
00:06:15.909 --> 00:06:19.046
- We took you as our regent...
- Betrayed it?

122
00:06:19.079 --> 00:06:22.015
...on the promise that you
would not take another husband.

123
00:06:22.049 --> 00:06:23.751
My children need a father.

124
00:06:23.784 --> 00:06:26.420
And who I take to my bed
is my own province

125
00:06:26.453 --> 00:06:27.955
and not the business
of this council.

126
00:06:27.988 --> 00:06:30.390
It's every bit our business!

127
00:06:31.425 --> 00:06:34.528
Did your brother
put you up to this. huh?

128
00:06:34.561 --> 00:06:37.164
The Douglases have always
licked the balls of England.

129
00:06:37.397 --> 00:06:39.133
Is this his secret plan
to rule us?

130
00:06:39.166 --> 00:06:40.467
King Henry doesn't even know.

131
00:06:40.501 --> 00:06:41.544
And Angus will not rule with me.

132
00:06:41.568 --> 00:06:43.504
I am regent with my son.

133
00:06:43.537 --> 00:06:45.038
Angus is only my husband.

134
00:06:45.072 --> 00:06:46.673
Oh. and that's what he told you.
is it?

135
00:06:47.808 --> 00:06:50.677
And you. you'd be happy
with that. would you.

136
00:06:50.711 --> 00:06:51.945
eh. Angus?

137
00:06:51.979 --> 00:06:54.114
Having some wee lassie
tell you what to do?

138
00:06:54.148 --> 00:06:56.650
I married her for love
in God's eyes.

139
00:06:56.683 --> 00:06:58.652
- as she did me.
- No.

140
00:06:59.653 --> 00:07:03.490
My brother. the duke of Albany.
will be summoned

141
00:07:03.524 --> 00:07:07.594
back from France. and you
will cede the regency to him.

142
00:07:07.628 --> 00:07:08.829
He will govern Scotland.

143
00:07:08.862 --> 00:07:11.799
Over my dead body. I am queen!

144
00:07:11.832 --> 00:07:14.034
He will take custody

145
00:07:14.067 --> 00:07:17.805
of Princes James and Alexander.

146
00:07:18.939 --> 00:07:22.576
We won't have our country
ruled by this prick.

147
00:07:22.609 --> 00:07:24.545
Hey! Get back here!

148
00:07:28.549 --> 00:07:29.950
Angus. run!

149
00:07:29.983 --> 00:07:31.618
What are we doing?

150
00:07:31.652 --> 00:07:32.692
Get back here!

151
00:07:32.719 --> 00:07:34.121
You bastard!

152
00:07:34.955 --> 00:07:38.025
Angus. you get James.
Alexander. darling.

153
00:07:38.058 --> 00:07:39.435
They should not
defy you. Your Grace.

154
00:07:39.459 --> 00:07:41.061
Quickly.

155
00:07:41.094 --> 00:07:42.462
Down the stairs. now!

156
00:07:42.496 --> 00:07:43.497
Down the stairs!

157
00:07:43.530 --> 00:07:44.598
Down!

158
00:07:44.631 --> 00:07:45.842
You bastard! Stay where you are!

159
00:07:45.866 --> 00:07:48.535
Angus. you bastard!

160
00:07:48.569 --> 00:07:49.703
Get back here!

161
00:07:50.904 --> 00:07:52.806
Get out! Get out!

162
00:07:52.840 --> 00:07:55.008
You tricked us!
Both of you tricked...

163
00:07:55.843 --> 00:07:57.945
Move it! Out of the way!

164
00:08:00.247 --> 00:08:03.183
You will rue the day
that you challenged me!

165
00:08:03.217 --> 00:08:06.486
I am regent with
full support of England

166
00:08:06.520 --> 00:08:08.255
and Spain through Catherine.

167
00:08:09.656 --> 00:08:11.625
You are dead men from this day.

168
00:08:11.658 --> 00:08:13.961
and they will... they will burn
your entrails

169
00:08:13.994 --> 00:08:15.762
for disrespecting me.

170
00:08:15.796 --> 00:08:16.864
Will they?

171
00:08:16.897 --> 00:08:18.498
Can anyone in your family

172
00:08:18.532 --> 00:08:20.267
be trusted to convey a letter?

173
00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:21.668
My Uncle Gavin.

174
00:08:21.702 --> 00:08:23.462
He'll come soon enough
when he hears of this.

175
00:08:23.503 --> 00:08:25.138
Watch at the window for him.

176
00:08:25.172 --> 00:08:27.074
You will write your brother
for his help?

177
00:08:27.107 --> 00:08:28.542
I will do more than that.

178
00:08:28.575 --> 00:08:31.612
I will write to Catherine.

179
00:08:40.053 --> 00:08:41.255
Henry.

180
00:08:41.288 --> 00:08:44.157
- Catherine?
- Your Grace.

181
00:08:44.191 --> 00:08:45.626
Is it the child?

182
00:08:45.659 --> 00:08:47.060
No. no.

183
00:08:47.094 --> 00:08:49.062
No. he is quite well.

184
00:08:50.564 --> 00:08:52.532
It is another matter.

185
00:08:53.600 --> 00:08:55.168
I must speak with you
in private.

186
00:09:03.644 --> 00:09:05.145
Your sister writes to me. She...

187
00:09:05.178 --> 00:09:07.014
About her hatred
of her fat French husband.

188
00:09:07.047 --> 00:09:09.549
- This is not news. Catherine.
- Not Mary.

189
00:09:09.583 --> 00:09:10.918
Meg.

190
00:09:12.786 --> 00:09:15.055
She has remarried.

191
00:09:15.088 --> 00:09:17.224
Archibald Douglas.
the earl of Angus.

192
00:09:17.257 --> 00:09:18.325
She has done what?

193
00:09:18.558 --> 00:09:19.993
The Scots are up in arms
about it.

194
00:09:20.027 --> 00:09:21.507
saying they will terminate
her regency

195
00:09:21.561 --> 00:09:22.863
in favor of the duke of Albany.

196
00:09:22.896 --> 00:09:24.865
whom they have summoned
back from France.

197
00:09:25.999 --> 00:09:28.201
What in God's name
is the matter with her?

198
00:09:28.235 --> 00:09:30.237
After everything
I've done for her.

199
00:09:30.270 --> 00:09:32.940
this is how she shows me thanks?

200
00:09:32.973 --> 00:09:35.075
She asks for you
to send an army.

201
00:09:35.108 --> 00:09:38.612
But. uh. to make it clear

202
00:09:38.645 --> 00:09:40.580
they come in peace.

203
00:09:42.015 --> 00:09:43.884
An army?

204
00:09:43.917 --> 00:09:45.052
In peace?

205
00:09:46.186 --> 00:09:47.988
How do I signal that?

206
00:09:48.021 --> 00:09:50.057
- Put them all in dresses?
- I know.

207
00:09:50.090 --> 00:09:51.725
The Scots would think
I'd invaded.

208
00:09:51.758 --> 00:09:54.194
- Yes. I know.
- I gave her one instruction.

209
00:09:54.227 --> 00:09:56.863
Keep England's peace
with Scotland for me.

210
00:10:01.702 --> 00:10:04.838
And now she writes
all this to you and not me.

211
00:10:04.871 --> 00:10:06.940
You are carrying my heir.

212
00:10:08.342 --> 00:10:11.211
She risks your health
and his survival.

213
00:10:13.213 --> 00:10:15.282
No. I will do nothing for her.

214
00:10:15.315 --> 00:10:17.150
Do not reply.

215
00:10:20.187 --> 00:10:23.023
You may go back and rest.

216
00:10:36.036 --> 00:10:38.138
<i>Dearest Mary.</i>

217
00:10:38.171 --> 00:10:40.407
<i>your sister is in trouble.</i>

218
00:10:40.640 --> 00:10:42.209
<i>and she needs your help.</i>

219
00:10:42.242 --> 00:10:46.246
<i>You must find a way to keep
the duke of Albany in France.</i>

220
00:10:47.381 --> 00:10:50.751
<i>Remind him of the cold
and inhospitable climate</i>

221
00:10:50.784 --> 00:10:53.286
<i>of his native land</i>

222
00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:56.923
<i>and the beauty and favors
France can offer.</i>

223
00:10:56.957 --> 00:10:58.992
<i>should he choose
to linger there.</i>

224
00:11:00.727 --> 00:11:03.430
<i>Meg will thank you
for your help.</i>

225
00:11:03.663 --> 00:11:05.766
<i>And I will too.</i>

226
00:11:05.799 --> 00:11:08.668
<i>From your sister Catherine.</i>

227
00:11:12.906 --> 00:11:15.442
Queen Mary of France.

228
00:11:15.675 --> 00:11:18.678
And please tell Thomas Howard
that I would like to see him.

229
00:11:27.687 --> 00:11:29.823
Good shot. Sire.

230
00:11:29.856 --> 00:11:31.667
Skewered him right through
the heart. Your Grace.

231
00:11:31.691 --> 00:11:34.227
The captain here taught me well
in my younger days.

232
00:11:34.261 --> 00:11:35.996
It is easy
to guide the eye of one

233
00:11:36.029 --> 00:11:39.032
with such a gift as yours.
Your Grace.

234
00:11:39.933 --> 00:11:42.135
Are you a keen huntswoman.
Lady Pole?

235
00:11:42.169 --> 00:11:46.139
I am not.
I see no joy in a kill.

236
00:11:46.173 --> 00:11:47.841
But I think my daughter's suitor

237
00:11:47.874 --> 00:11:49.709
has commitment for us all.

238
00:11:49.743 --> 00:11:51.044
You got it!

239
00:11:51.078 --> 00:11:52.879
Do you eat meat.
though. Lady Pole.

240
00:11:52.913 --> 00:11:54.414
do you not?

241
00:11:54.448 --> 00:11:56.483
I do.

242
00:11:56.716 --> 00:11:59.086
For many years.
there was no food in my belly

243
00:11:59.119 --> 00:12:01.188
or in the bellies
of my children.

244
00:12:01.221 --> 00:12:03.290
Because I suffered
when my husband died.

245
00:12:04.424 --> 00:12:06.726
Now God and king
both smile on you

246
00:12:06.760 --> 00:12:08.795
and bless you with a match

247
00:12:08.829 --> 00:12:10.997
to our most faithful servant.
Compton.

248
00:12:14.868 --> 00:12:16.069
Do you not shoot?

249
00:12:16.103 --> 00:12:18.805
This is low game. my lady.

250
00:12:18.839 --> 00:12:23.143
Rabbits are dirty creatures.
and they breed too readily.

251
00:12:24.211 --> 00:12:25.879
But for your sake.
I will desist today

252
00:12:25.912 --> 00:12:26.880
from any bloodshed.

253
00:12:26.913 --> 00:12:28.048
Watch out.

254
00:12:31.952 --> 00:12:33.854
Felled by a woman. Compton?

255
00:12:33.887 --> 00:12:36.323
My sister.
That makes sense. actually.

256
00:12:36.356 --> 00:12:37.867
We should've put
a bobtail on him.

257
00:12:37.891 --> 00:12:39.092
make a proper sport of it.

258
00:12:40.360 --> 00:12:43.497
That was quite amusing
for you. Wiltshire.

259
00:12:45.298 --> 00:12:47.000
Perhaps the lady might do better

260
00:12:47.033 --> 00:12:49.169
to aim at her own husband.

261
00:12:49.202 --> 00:12:51.972
I think it is his attention
that she fails to win.

262
00:12:52.005 --> 00:12:53.874
I will remove myself from range.

263
00:12:57.978 --> 00:12:59.989
The Scots will already
think that Meg's marriage

264
00:13:00.013 --> 00:13:01.524
to a Douglas is my attempt
to rule them.

265
00:13:01.548 --> 00:13:03.250
Never mind me sending
an army to help.

266
00:13:03.283 --> 00:13:05.452
Your Grace is wise to resist.

267
00:13:05.485 --> 00:13:08.388
Women's fancies
blow too hot for reason.

268
00:13:08.421 --> 00:13:11.992
They are sentimental creatures.
and to have one rule a country.

269
00:13:12.025 --> 00:13:15.462
even though she is your sister.
it is a disaster.

270
00:13:15.495 --> 00:13:18.365
I disagree.

271
00:13:18.398 --> 00:13:20.467
All of my daughters
are educated in the classics

272
00:13:20.500 --> 00:13:22.502
and they have finer minds
than many men I know.

273
00:13:22.536 --> 00:13:23.937
certainly more reason.

274
00:13:26.439 --> 00:13:30.377
Has Your Grace considered
my humble supplication?

275
00:13:32.212 --> 00:13:33.947
Yes. uh. Lord Chancellor.

276
00:13:35.248 --> 00:13:36.559
The queen worries
another promotion

277
00:13:36.583 --> 00:13:39.085
would go to your head. Wolsey.

278
00:13:41.021 --> 00:13:42.923
Oh. dear.

279
00:13:42.956 --> 00:13:45.492
A lady much in need of guidance.

280
00:13:45.525 --> 00:13:50.030
Perhaps Your Grace's
expert hand would be the thing.

281
00:13:57.571 --> 00:13:59.039
Lady Anne.

282
00:13:59.072 --> 00:14:00.574
Yes. Your Grace?

283
00:14:00.607 --> 00:14:03.543
Perhaps I could show you
how to win your prey.

284
00:14:03.577 --> 00:14:05.512
What is his interest
in Anne Hastings?

285
00:14:05.545 --> 00:14:07.614
Wolsey still believes
he is in battle with the queen

286
00:14:07.847 --> 00:14:09.182
for the king's favor.

287
00:14:09.216 --> 00:14:11.284
So if he can drive a wedge
between them.

288
00:14:11.318 --> 00:14:14.187
then Queen Catherine's
influence is greatly reduced.

289
00:14:15.388 --> 00:14:17.123
Oh. Lady Pole.
I would have thought

290
00:14:17.157 --> 00:14:19.593
that court politics
no longer surprised you.

291
00:14:19.626 --> 00:14:22.062
Surprise me. no. But pain me?

292
00:14:23.330 --> 00:14:26.433
Reggie has been sent away
in the guise

293
00:14:26.466 --> 00:14:28.401
of his best interests. but...

294
00:14:28.435 --> 00:14:31.404
it feels like
a punishment to me.

295
00:14:31.438 --> 00:14:33.907
You are too good for us all.

296
00:14:47.320 --> 00:14:50.123
I'm sorry
that my shooting is so poor.

297
00:14:50.156 --> 00:14:52.325
I'm very grateful for
your guidance. Your Highness.

298
00:14:53.426 --> 00:14:54.427
My pleasure.

299
00:14:58.932 --> 00:14:59.966
Wolsey.

300
00:15:10.110 --> 00:15:12.279
My lord.

301
00:15:25.492 --> 00:15:26.559
Henry.

302
00:15:29.195 --> 00:15:32.432
I believe that I have solved
your sister's woes in Scotland.

303
00:15:34.601 --> 00:15:38.071
No. we cannot send an army. no.

304
00:15:38.104 --> 00:15:40.073
but what if
General Thomas Howard

305
00:15:40.106 --> 00:15:42.175
were to ride out
with a small retinue

306
00:15:42.208 --> 00:15:44.044
and negotiate her position?

307
00:15:46.012 --> 00:15:48.348
It would not be
a show of force but...

308
00:15:48.381 --> 00:15:50.183
implies we may take
a stronger line

309
00:15:50.216 --> 00:15:52.018
if this is not resolved.

310
00:15:53.420 --> 00:15:55.255
But I said I choose not to.

311
00:15:57.190 --> 00:15:58.591
Henry. you cannot
leave your sister

312
00:15:58.625 --> 00:16:00.627
at the mercy of the Scots.

313
00:16:02.696 --> 00:16:06.099
I would gladly leave my sister
to the mercy of all demons

314
00:16:06.132 --> 00:16:07.233
for what she did to me

315
00:16:07.267 --> 00:16:09.736
in marrying
that halfwit in a kilt.

316
00:16:15.508 --> 00:16:20.513
Well. that's unfortunate.
as Howard is already riding.

317
00:16:24.117 --> 00:16:26.219
I had no choice.

318
00:16:26.252 --> 00:16:28.421
We couldn't leave her there.

319
00:16:31.691 --> 00:16:33.393
Why would you disobey me

320
00:16:33.426 --> 00:16:36.029
when I clearly told you
my instruction?

321
00:16:38.131 --> 00:16:39.265
Wolsey's right.

322
00:16:39.299 --> 00:16:41.468
Women should not govern
a country

323
00:16:41.501 --> 00:16:43.636
when they cannot even govern
their own sentiment.

324
00:16:43.670 --> 00:16:45.138
Wolsey said that?

325
00:16:47.273 --> 00:16:49.275
With what provocation?

326
00:16:51.678 --> 00:16:54.547
- Which lady did he criticize?
- Well. he's right.

327
00:16:55.648 --> 00:16:59.052
What the archbishop
calls sentiment

328
00:16:59.085 --> 00:17:01.020
is cold. hard common sense.

329
00:17:02.355 --> 00:17:04.195
If you leave your sister
locked up in a pantry.

330
00:17:04.224 --> 00:17:06.092
then the Scots see you as weak.

331
00:17:06.693 --> 00:17:09.129
A peaceful Scotland
is what England needs.

332
00:17:09.162 --> 00:17:11.798
which means your sister's
sons must take the throne.

333
00:17:13.333 --> 00:17:16.035
If Albany returns.
then they will not.

334
00:17:17.537 --> 00:17:19.506
Henry. you must do
as you see fit.

335
00:17:19.539 --> 00:17:21.174
But Howard is already riding.

336
00:17:21.207 --> 00:17:22.551
so claim this outcome
for yourself.

337
00:17:22.575 --> 00:17:25.578
or blame me for it. as you wish.

338
00:17:28.381 --> 00:17:31.184
Did you deny Wolsey the
position of lord chancellor?

339
00:17:32.485 --> 00:17:33.753
I said I'd think on it.

340
00:17:33.787 --> 00:17:35.789
Well. perhaps you'll weigh up

341
00:17:35.822 --> 00:17:38.324
which of us
is being led by sentiment.

342
00:17:51.771 --> 00:17:53.440
As you know. my sister Meg

343
00:17:53.473 --> 00:17:55.642
has rashly made a marriage

344
00:17:55.675 --> 00:17:58.445
that has compromised
her regency.

345
00:17:58.478 --> 00:18:01.581
I've sent a troop of soldiers
up to Scotland.

346
00:18:01.614 --> 00:18:04.717
under the stewardship
of General Thomas Howard.

347
00:18:04.751 --> 00:18:06.619
Make sure he doesn't
nod off on the way.

348
00:18:06.653 --> 00:18:08.455
Although I have
written to Howard.

349
00:18:08.488 --> 00:18:10.356
telling him to take his time.

350
00:18:10.390 --> 00:18:12.725
It will do my sister good
to think on what she's done

351
00:18:12.759 --> 00:18:15.428
before she's reinstated
on the throne.

352
00:18:15.462 --> 00:18:17.697
Bloody Scots.
Have they forgotten Flodden?

353
00:18:17.730 --> 00:18:20.433
You do well to remind them
of England's might. Your Grace.

354
00:18:20.467 --> 00:18:22.635
England will not be intimidated.

355
00:18:22.669 --> 00:18:24.771
We are mighty.

356
00:18:24.804 --> 00:18:27.207
We will be obeyed.

357
00:18:28.374 --> 00:18:30.343
And soon we will have an heir.

358
00:18:31.611 --> 00:18:34.414
God blesses us...

359
00:18:34.447 --> 00:18:36.516
and He will keep us.

360
00:18:36.549 --> 00:18:37.884
God save the king.

361
00:18:38.117 --> 00:18:39.285
God save the king.

362
00:18:39.319 --> 00:18:41.421
God save the king.

363
00:18:41.454 --> 00:18:43.389
God save Queen Catherine.

364
00:18:43.423 --> 00:18:45.291
God save Queen Catherine.

365
00:18:47.694 --> 00:18:49.829
God save the king.

366
00:18:49.863 --> 00:18:52.298
God save Queen Catherine.

367
00:18:52.332 --> 00:18:54.300
England prays for you.

368
00:18:54.334 --> 00:18:57.237
God blesses us.

369
00:18:57.270 --> 00:19:00.607
The heir in my belly proves
he finds us worthy and devout.

370
00:19:02.442 --> 00:19:05.411
And a. uh. new direction

371
00:19:05.445 --> 00:19:08.448
on your sister's predicament.

372
00:19:09.516 --> 00:19:13.152
The king showed her his mercy.

373
00:19:34.841 --> 00:19:37.410
Anne Hastings
looks quite radiant.

374
00:19:37.443 --> 00:19:40.246
Has she found a man
to warm her bed?

375
00:19:40.280 --> 00:19:41.814
I do not know. Highness.

376
00:19:41.848 --> 00:19:43.950
Oviedo has not heard?

377
00:19:44.183 --> 00:19:45.728
He is friendly now
with the men at court.

378
00:19:45.752 --> 00:19:48.488
and they surely share
such gossip.

379
00:19:48.521 --> 00:19:51.391
Oviedo does not set much store
to idle gossip.

380
00:19:51.424 --> 00:19:52.792
Catherine.

381
00:19:56.329 --> 00:19:57.797
I'll go with you to your rooms.

382
00:19:57.830 --> 00:19:59.232
Hmm.

383
00:20:04.237 --> 00:20:07.206
The court was giddy
at our power.

384
00:20:07.240 --> 00:20:09.275
They were quite roused by it.

385
00:20:09.309 --> 00:20:11.945
And I... by you.

386
00:20:11.978 --> 00:20:15.915
- Catherine. you have...
- Come. let me have you.

387
00:20:15.949 --> 00:20:17.850
I have wanted you all day.

388
00:20:26.659 --> 00:20:29.629
Catherine. you must
take to your confinement.

389
00:20:31.931 --> 00:20:33.333
No. it is too early.

390
00:20:33.366 --> 00:20:35.868
Our son must have
the best chance to be strong.

391
00:20:35.902 --> 00:20:38.404
He does not need the strains
and racket of the court.

392
00:20:44.877 --> 00:20:47.313
Did Wolsey counsel you to this?

393
00:20:48.014 --> 00:20:49.515
Wolsey knows his place.

394
00:20:49.549 --> 00:20:51.985
He would not presume
to instruct me.

395
00:20:52.018 --> 00:20:54.487
I caution you to observe
the same. Catherine.

396
00:20:56.389 --> 00:20:59.959
Henry. I carry the future king.
and I want what's best for him.

397
00:20:59.993 --> 00:21:02.295
- In that. we are united.
- Good. then it's settled.

398
00:21:02.328 --> 00:21:03.896
Please. please.

399
00:21:03.930 --> 00:21:06.666
grant me till
All Saints' Day at least?

400
00:21:07.900 --> 00:21:11.404
So I may attend Mass
and pray to God

401
00:21:11.437 --> 00:21:14.707
that he bears our son
safely into our arms...

402
00:21:16.643 --> 00:21:18.745
...and keeps him there.

403
00:21:22.915 --> 00:21:24.050
Of course.

404
00:21:25.685 --> 00:21:27.487
You may have until then.

405
00:21:31.057 --> 00:21:33.626
And then we'll have our son.

406
00:21:40.600 --> 00:21:42.402
What delays your uncle?

407
00:21:42.435 --> 00:21:44.303
Where is our reply from England?

408
00:21:47.306 --> 00:21:49.409
Perhaps he is helping
Catherine muster men...

409
00:21:50.610 --> 00:21:51.911
...or persuading my brother.

410
00:21:52.945 --> 00:21:56.049
He will be so angry with me.

411
00:21:56.082 --> 00:21:59.485
but Catherine will
soon soothe his hot head.

412
00:21:59.519 --> 00:22:02.522
Angus. Angus. come here.

413
00:22:08.428 --> 00:22:09.862
Your Grace.

414
00:22:09.896 --> 00:22:12.598
Oh. Gavin.
You have word from England?

415
00:22:12.632 --> 00:22:14.100
Uncle. what news?

416
00:22:14.333 --> 00:22:16.669
A letter
from General Thomas Howard.

417
00:22:16.703 --> 00:22:19.505
Alexander Stewart's got
his thugs out here patrolling.

418
00:22:19.539 --> 00:22:21.741
I had to make a show
of demanding your release

419
00:22:21.774 --> 00:22:23.342
so they didn't wonder
why I'd come.

420
00:22:23.376 --> 00:22:25.411
Uncle. you have our gratitude.

421
00:22:25.445 --> 00:22:27.447
Perhaps our queen will
reward you with a castle.

422
00:22:27.480 --> 00:22:28.881
There is no army.

423
00:22:29.749 --> 00:22:32.452
General Thomas Howard
rides to us with six men.

424
00:22:32.485 --> 00:22:34.120
Six?

425
00:22:34.353 --> 00:22:36.522
Albany has been kept in France.

426
00:22:36.556 --> 00:22:38.491
Howard instructs us
to inform the Scots

427
00:22:38.524 --> 00:22:40.793
that I am regent and if they
do not let me rule.

428
00:22:40.827 --> 00:22:42.562
England will lay waste
to Scotland.

429
00:22:42.595 --> 00:22:44.097
Six hundred men? Or six?

430
00:22:44.130 --> 00:22:46.065
There is the threat
of further force.

431
00:22:46.099 --> 00:22:47.643
There is no threat at all.
We are abandoned.

432
00:22:47.667 --> 00:22:49.135
- Angus!
- Not now.

433
00:22:49.368 --> 00:22:51.137
I cannot help you.

434
00:22:51.370 --> 00:22:52.505
Angus.

435
00:22:52.538 --> 00:22:55.541
That is my son. our future king.

436
00:22:55.575 --> 00:22:56.943
you raise your voice to.

437
00:22:56.976 --> 00:22:58.845
Aye. a king.
and yet here we are.

438
00:22:58.878 --> 00:23:01.748
Locked up and left to perish
like slaves. not sovereigns.

439
00:23:03.416 --> 00:23:06.619
I am sovereign. Angus.

440
00:23:06.652 --> 00:23:07.963
And if you thought
that marrying me

441
00:23:07.987 --> 00:23:09.956
would be an easy life.
then you are a fool.

442
00:23:18.931 --> 00:23:20.933
We must be strong.

443
00:23:26.105 --> 00:23:30.643
When we first spoke
in the chapel.

444
00:23:30.676 --> 00:23:34.580
it felt like poetry...

445
00:23:34.614 --> 00:23:35.915
magic.

446
00:23:38.684 --> 00:23:42.555
I was surrounded by brute force.

447
00:23:43.956 --> 00:23:45.558
And then there was you.

448
00:23:46.592 --> 00:23:50.463
You opened your heart to me.

449
00:23:51.964 --> 00:23:55.568
And I thought that made you
braver than...

450
00:23:55.601 --> 00:23:57.870
Than any of the warring men
in Scotland...

451
00:23:59.572 --> 00:24:02.041
...than any man

452
00:24:02.074 --> 00:24:03.910
I have ever known.

453
00:24:05.778 --> 00:24:07.747
So I kissed you.

454
00:24:20.560 --> 00:24:22.929
But perhaps I did not
see you clearly.

455
00:24:35.041 --> 00:24:38.477
And the fearsome beast
did rise up out of the well

456
00:24:38.511 --> 00:24:40.947
before the brave knights.
and agh!

457
00:24:40.980 --> 00:24:43.049
Yeah.

458
00:24:43.082 --> 00:24:48.020
Oviedo. you think it's true

459
00:24:48.054 --> 00:24:50.223
that the king
beds Anne Hastings?

460
00:24:50.256 --> 00:24:51.858
It is what everybody says.

461
00:24:51.891 --> 00:24:54.126
It is the way
of the English kings.

462
00:24:54.160 --> 00:24:56.128
They jump into so many beds.

463
00:24:57.196 --> 00:24:59.699
You are not knights.

464
00:24:59.732 --> 00:25:01.567
You are my little kings.

465
00:25:01.601 --> 00:25:03.936
- Not little kings.
- Oh. yes.

466
00:25:03.970 --> 00:25:07.173
Or perhaps you are thieves.

467
00:25:07.206 --> 00:25:08.908
for you have stolen my heart.

468
00:25:08.941 --> 00:25:11.510
- No.
- Yes.

469
00:25:11.544 --> 00:25:13.045
Look.

470
00:25:13.079 --> 00:25:15.248
It is gone. Ah!

471
00:26:40.366 --> 00:26:43.069
A confinement
can be a blessing. Highness.

472
00:26:45.237 --> 00:26:48.174
A chance for reflection
and for peace.

473
00:26:49.642 --> 00:26:51.243
Let me help you.

474
00:26:53.813 --> 00:26:55.181
Lina.

475
00:26:56.882 --> 00:26:58.951
Is there something I don't know?

476
00:27:00.820 --> 00:27:03.656
I... I don't understand.

477
00:27:05.057 --> 00:27:07.393
There are whispers.

478
00:27:07.626 --> 00:27:09.795
People speak about me.

479
00:27:09.829 --> 00:27:13.766
Yes. they speak about you
all the time.

480
00:27:13.799 --> 00:27:17.236
And their talk is of their
desire for your happiness

481
00:27:17.269 --> 00:27:19.105
and for your son and heir.

482
00:27:20.039 --> 00:27:22.108
I will fetch rosemary.

483
00:27:22.141 --> 00:27:23.342
Lina.

484
00:27:26.345 --> 00:27:27.780
We are friends.

485
00:27:28.714 --> 00:27:30.082
So you must tell me.

486
00:27:35.287 --> 00:27:36.789
When we first came to England.

487
00:27:36.822 --> 00:27:38.391
you told me that I am the light.

488
00:27:39.658 --> 00:27:40.926
You still are.

489
00:27:42.061 --> 00:27:44.230
A lantern burns as brightly
in a single room

490
00:27:44.263 --> 00:27:46.298
as in a whole court.

491
00:27:46.332 --> 00:27:47.767
I feel I am in darkness.

492
00:27:49.935 --> 00:27:51.937
What is it that I miss. please?

493
00:27:52.938 --> 00:27:54.740
I need to know.

494
00:27:58.878 --> 00:28:00.012
No.

495
00:28:03.349 --> 00:28:05.017
No. not Anne Hastings.

496
00:28:05.785 --> 00:28:08.087
- It is not Henry who she bed...
- Highness.

497
00:28:08.120 --> 00:28:10.322
these are foolish rumors
that people use

498
00:28:10.356 --> 00:28:12.324
to idle away their time.

499
00:28:12.358 --> 00:28:15.761
- Push them from your mind.
- But this is what is said.

500
00:28:18.364 --> 00:28:19.364
Lina!

501
00:28:28.307 --> 00:28:30.776
A woman was seen

502
00:28:30.810 --> 00:28:32.478
entering the king's rooms.

503
00:28:34.213 --> 00:28:36.782
Some say it was Anne Hastings.

504
00:28:38.918 --> 00:28:41.020
Catherine. Henry loves you.

505
00:28:41.053 --> 00:28:42.455
I know he loves me.

506
00:28:46.725 --> 00:28:50.930
I will not be that bitter...
jealous woman.

507
00:28:52.832 --> 00:28:54.800
I will not be my sister.

508
00:29:12.952 --> 00:29:14.820
- Yes.
- Please.

509
00:29:14.854 --> 00:29:16.856
What does that butcher's boy

510
00:29:16.889 --> 00:29:18.090
think he's doing?

511
00:29:18.124 --> 00:29:20.159
I've seen you chattering
with the king. Wiltshire.

512
00:29:20.192 --> 00:29:21.760
You're not above
your own maneuvers.

513
00:29:21.794 --> 00:29:22.938
No idea what you're...

514
00:29:22.962 --> 00:29:25.030
You're drunk. Brandon.

515
00:29:26.031 --> 00:29:28.968
Wolsey is shameless
in his machinations.

516
00:29:29.001 --> 00:29:30.803
Yes. and yet the king
responds to it.

517
00:29:30.836 --> 00:29:32.138
Yes.

518
00:29:32.171 --> 00:29:33.982
Lady Anne. perhaps
you'd like to make a toast

519
00:29:34.006 --> 00:29:35.341
to the newly promised couple.

520
00:29:35.374 --> 00:29:37.943
given that you are lady aunt
to the happy groom.

521
00:29:37.977 --> 00:29:40.312
I-I... if Your Grace wishes.

522
00:29:40.346 --> 00:29:41.380
Yes.

523
00:29:41.413 --> 00:29:43.883
To my nephew Henry Stafford

524
00:29:43.916 --> 00:29:45.985
and his betrothed. Ursula Pole.

525
00:29:46.018 --> 00:29:49.388
I wish you many children
and all the joys of love.

526
00:29:49.421 --> 00:29:50.956
Hear. hear.

527
00:29:50.990 --> 00:29:52.958
Hear. hear.

528
00:29:54.059 --> 00:29:56.428
The wedding night
is brutal. Ursula.

529
00:29:56.462 --> 00:29:59.031
Go easy on her. boy.

530
00:29:59.064 --> 00:30:01.233
But you will only
ever be a virgin once

531
00:30:01.267 --> 00:30:02.902
and will be glad
when it is passed.

532
00:30:02.935 --> 00:30:05.938
He won't.

533
00:30:05.971 --> 00:30:07.439
I mean to say...

534
00:30:07.473 --> 00:30:08.941
there will be blood.

535
00:30:10.342 --> 00:30:12.211
Well. not every maid
is thus afflicted.

536
00:30:12.244 --> 00:30:14.513
Oh. yes. they are.
The first time. yes.

537
00:30:21.053 --> 00:30:23.155
As mother to the bride.

538
00:30:23.189 --> 00:30:26.458
I would like to wish
Henry and Ursula good health.

539
00:30:26.492 --> 00:30:30.496
good fortunes.
and a nursery full of babies.

540
00:30:30.529 --> 00:30:33.165
- Your health.
- Your good health.

541
00:30:33.199 --> 00:30:35.100
To Wolsey's swift demise.

542
00:30:42.841 --> 00:30:44.176
Excuse me.

543
00:30:53.452 --> 00:30:56.956
The queen has heard a rumor

544
00:30:56.989 --> 00:31:00.960
that the king and Lady Hastings.

545
00:31:00.993 --> 00:31:03.162
that he beds her.

546
00:31:03.195 --> 00:31:05.197
Catherine is distressed.

547
00:31:05.231 --> 00:31:06.899
and I am worried for the baby.

548
00:31:07.633 --> 00:31:09.201
I am aware of it...

549
00:31:10.369 --> 00:31:13.372
...and of other talk
more dangerous to her.

550
00:31:13.405 --> 00:31:14.640
What talk?

551
00:31:14.873 --> 00:31:16.342
Of wedding nights

552
00:31:16.375 --> 00:31:18.577
and how maidenhood is proven.

553
00:31:20.246 --> 00:31:22.348
Leave it with me.

554
00:31:22.381 --> 00:31:24.383
I have had an idea
that may help.

555
00:31:25.517 --> 00:31:26.585
It is late.

556
00:31:26.619 --> 00:31:28.020
You should go home
to your family.

557
00:31:28.053 --> 00:31:30.289
Thank you. Lady Pole.

558
00:31:47.606 --> 00:31:49.074
I came to say good night.

559
00:32:03.322 --> 00:32:04.657
Is there. um...

560
00:32:06.558 --> 00:32:08.360
...any news of Meg?

561
00:32:08.394 --> 00:32:10.195
None that I've heard. no.

562
00:32:15.934 --> 00:32:17.603
Henry?

563
00:32:18.604 --> 00:32:20.539
I worship you...

564
00:32:20.572 --> 00:32:23.676
everything you do and are.

565
00:32:26.512 --> 00:32:29.281
And even when we cannot...

566
00:32:32.451 --> 00:32:33.585
...be together...

567
00:32:33.619 --> 00:32:35.954
Of course we cannot.
You are with child.

568
00:32:35.988 --> 00:32:39.024
...I know
that you have appetites...

569
00:32:40.592 --> 00:32:43.595
...that I cannot fulfil for now.

570
00:32:45.130 --> 00:32:48.500
So if you take
another woman to your bed.

571
00:32:48.534 --> 00:32:50.002
then I would understand.

572
00:32:52.471 --> 00:32:54.273
But I would sooner that...

573
00:32:56.008 --> 00:32:57.543
...that you told me.

574
00:32:57.576 --> 00:32:59.978
Another woman?

575
00:33:00.012 --> 00:33:02.648
If you shared it
with me. then...

576
00:33:05.384 --> 00:33:07.619
...it would be something
that is ours...

577
00:33:08.987 --> 00:33:10.756
...together...

578
00:33:12.191 --> 00:33:14.093
...of our love.

579
00:33:14.126 --> 00:33:16.662
And then people
wouldn't pity me.

580
00:33:16.695 --> 00:33:18.530
I know

581
00:33:18.564 --> 00:33:22.034
that what we share is different

582
00:33:22.067 --> 00:33:24.269
and this is of the flesh.

583
00:33:26.572 --> 00:33:29.475
But I would rather
that I heard it first from you.

584
00:33:35.414 --> 00:33:38.250
There is nothing to tell.

585
00:33:40.052 --> 00:33:42.521
You're tired.

586
00:33:42.554 --> 00:33:43.756
You must rest.

587
00:34:17.556 --> 00:34:19.758
Stare at me all you like.

588
00:34:19.792 --> 00:34:22.694
I am indeed
a handsome old devil.

589
00:34:24.663 --> 00:34:27.166
You bog-dwelling fuckers.

590
00:34:27.199 --> 00:34:28.434
<i>Howard is here.</i>

591
00:34:28.467 --> 00:34:31.403
We will negotiate my position.

592
00:34:31.437 --> 00:34:32.771
We are coming out.

593
00:34:32.805 --> 00:34:36.108
We will go to Stirling
and resolve this with civility.

594
00:34:37.776 --> 00:34:38.776
Angus.

595
00:34:58.864 --> 00:35:00.499
There are six Englishmen outside

596
00:35:00.532 --> 00:35:01.800
whom I will speak with.

597
00:35:01.834 --> 00:35:05.103
Lay a finger on me. and they
will quarter you alive.

598
00:35:16.114 --> 00:35:18.194
- Stay back. Douglas.
- I need to explain it. though.

599
00:35:24.156 --> 00:35:25.691
Queen Margaret.

600
00:35:25.724 --> 00:35:28.160
I bring you greetings
from the queen.

601
00:35:28.193 --> 00:35:31.463
General Howard. I'm...
I am very glad to see you.

602
00:35:31.497 --> 00:35:33.632
And I you. Your Grace.

603
00:35:33.665 --> 00:35:35.534
Have you been sleeping
in a gorse bush?

604
00:35:37.703 --> 00:35:40.706
Let us go to Stirling
to discuss my regency.

605
00:35:43.308 --> 00:35:45.444
No. No. no. what are you...
What are you doing?

606
00:35:45.477 --> 00:35:47.212
No! No!

607
00:35:47.246 --> 00:35:49.147
Give them back to me!
Give them back to me!

608
00:35:49.181 --> 00:35:50.682
Unhand those boys!

609
00:35:50.716 --> 00:35:52.317
I give you fair warning.

610
00:35:52.351 --> 00:35:53.862
You don't want to make
an enemy of England.

611
00:35:53.886 --> 00:35:55.654
Angus!

612
00:35:55.687 --> 00:35:58.590
You sniveling wretch.
you bring them back to me!

613
00:35:58.624 --> 00:35:59.634
It's better for you. Meg.

614
00:35:59.658 --> 00:36:01.260
This way.
they'll show you mercy.

615
00:36:01.293 --> 00:36:04.196
Oh. for me? For my sake?

616
00:36:04.229 --> 00:36:06.265
Bollocks.

617
00:36:06.298 --> 00:36:07.633
Get on the horse. Your Grace.

618
00:36:07.666 --> 00:36:08.810
- Get on it now.
- No. No.

619
00:36:08.834 --> 00:36:10.802
No. I cannot leave my boys.

620
00:36:10.836 --> 00:36:14.673
If you want to live to see
your children again. then ride.

621
00:36:20.712 --> 00:36:22.748
Up. up.

622
00:36:55.814 --> 00:36:58.283
Queen Margaret.

623
00:37:00.285 --> 00:37:04.423
If I could cut out
my weak and stupid heart.

624
00:37:04.456 --> 00:37:08.226
my foolish and shameful need
for love. I would do it.

625
00:37:08.260 --> 00:37:11.530
I have lost my boys!

626
00:37:13.332 --> 00:37:15.334
I have betrayed them.

627
00:37:16.902 --> 00:37:18.971
How could I be so stupid?

628
00:37:20.339 --> 00:37:22.240
You were lonely.

629
00:37:22.274 --> 00:37:24.843
I trusted him.

630
00:37:24.876 --> 00:37:26.511
and he betrayed me.

631
00:37:27.813 --> 00:37:30.349
I will never trust again.

632
00:37:30.382 --> 00:37:32.884
You will return for them.

633
00:37:32.918 --> 00:37:35.354
You're a fucking she-wolf.

634
00:37:40.892 --> 00:37:43.895
I will not let my brother
see me cry.

635
00:37:43.929 --> 00:37:46.531
We will ride to York first.

636
00:37:46.565 --> 00:37:48.767
I will stay there
until I'm ready.

637
00:37:56.942 --> 00:37:58.910
To York!

638
00:38:09.354 --> 00:38:10.822
Thank you.

639
00:38:12.324 --> 00:38:13.759
Sir Compton.

640
00:38:13.792 --> 00:38:14.793
William.

641
00:38:15.927 --> 00:38:17.896
I've asked you here
to join me because...

642
00:38:17.929 --> 00:38:19.031
And I was very pleased

643
00:38:19.064 --> 00:38:21.867
to receive your invitation.
Lady Pole.

644
00:38:23.468 --> 00:38:25.837
There is a delicate matter.

645
00:38:25.871 --> 00:38:27.673
The queen is in distress.

646
00:38:27.706 --> 00:38:30.809
and I fear it may harm
her unborn heir.

647
00:38:30.842 --> 00:38:34.713
I was hoping I might
seek your help.

648
00:38:34.746 --> 00:38:37.382
Madam. you shall have it.

649
00:38:38.316 --> 00:38:42.521
The matter
that so troubles her is...

650
00:38:42.554 --> 00:38:44.956
Well. I'm sure
you've heard the rumors

651
00:38:44.990 --> 00:38:47.059
about the king and Lady Anne.

652
00:38:47.092 --> 00:38:49.594
I admit I am aware of them.

653
00:38:49.628 --> 00:38:51.797
The only proof is that
a lady of her likeness

654
00:38:51.830 --> 00:38:54.366
was seen exiting
the king's room.

655
00:38:54.399 --> 00:38:56.435
But it strikes me.
we could start

656
00:38:56.468 --> 00:38:59.504
the court's tongues wagging
on a different story.

657
00:39:00.672 --> 00:39:03.075
That the gentleman
she was there to see

658
00:39:03.108 --> 00:39:04.876
was not the king at all...

659
00:39:06.411 --> 00:39:08.013
...but his groom.

660
00:39:11.016 --> 00:39:12.818
But that's...

661
00:39:12.851 --> 00:39:15.554
You are the only other gentleman

662
00:39:15.587 --> 00:39:17.022
in the king's rooms.

663
00:39:17.055 --> 00:39:18.957
If we could persuade the court
that it was you

664
00:39:18.990 --> 00:39:20.492
she was there to see.

665
00:39:20.525 --> 00:39:22.894
then the king would be
quite blameless.

666
00:39:22.928 --> 00:39:26.398
and Queen Catherine's
broken heart would be restored.

667
00:39:27.399 --> 00:39:31.436
Madam. this is difficult. that...

668
00:39:31.470 --> 00:39:32.838
To meddle
in the king's affairs...

669
00:39:32.871 --> 00:39:35.373
The king would not want
his queen and heir

670
00:39:35.407 --> 00:39:38.944
to be burdened by his appetites.

671
00:39:38.977 --> 00:39:42.481
We cannot ask him to desist.
but...

672
00:39:42.514 --> 00:39:46.518
this would bring
a resolution to the matter.

673
00:39:50.021 --> 00:39:53.091
Madam. I find your loyalty
to the queen most laudable.

674
00:39:53.125 --> 00:39:54.760
Hmm.

675
00:39:54.793 --> 00:39:56.695
If this wins me your favor

676
00:39:56.728 --> 00:39:58.063
and helps our royal heir

677
00:39:58.096 --> 00:40:00.832
arrive more peaceably
in the world.

678
00:40:00.866 --> 00:40:02.701
then I will do my part.

679
00:40:03.802 --> 00:40:06.538
You are the most remarkably
selfless woman.

680
00:40:26.057 --> 00:40:27.526
Is it the baby. Your Grace?

681
00:40:30.028 --> 00:40:31.530
It is nothing.

682
00:40:32.864 --> 00:40:34.866
I am quite well.

683
00:41:17.609 --> 00:41:18.944
Lady Hastings.

684
00:41:20.111 --> 00:41:22.247
Lady Pole.

685
00:41:22.480 --> 00:41:25.817
It seems the better woman
has won.

686
00:41:25.851 --> 00:41:27.519
Sir William Compton
hasn't been able

687
00:41:27.552 --> 00:41:29.788
take his eyes from you
all night.

688
00:41:29.821 --> 00:41:34.092
I will not demean myself
trying to compete with you.

689
00:41:34.125 --> 00:41:35.994
You are young and beautiful.

690
00:41:36.027 --> 00:41:39.531
Sir William is clearly besotted.

691
00:41:46.805 --> 00:41:48.607
Lady Anne.

692
00:41:49.674 --> 00:41:53.078
I have long admired you
from afar.

693
00:41:55.547 --> 00:41:56.781
Shall we?

694
00:42:12.831 --> 00:42:14.833
Oh. Your Grace.

695
00:42:17.702 --> 00:42:19.213
No. he is coming too early.

696
00:42:19.237 --> 00:42:21.640
Go and fetch Lina.

697
00:42:21.673 --> 00:42:24.142
Go! Quickly.

698
00:42:26.211 --> 00:42:28.079
No.

699
00:42:28.113 --> 00:42:30.148
Please. please. please.

700
00:42:30.181 --> 00:42:31.549
<i>Where is Lina?</i>

701
00:42:32.717 --> 00:42:34.085
Is she here?

702
00:42:38.690 --> 00:42:39.891
Lina!

703
00:42:39.925 --> 00:42:41.092
Lina.

704
00:42:42.093 --> 00:42:43.795
Lina. the queen
is calling for you.

705
00:42:43.828 --> 00:42:44.796
Quickly!

706
00:42:44.829 --> 00:42:46.131
The baby comes?

707
00:42:52.203 --> 00:42:54.072
Catherine. I'm here.

708
00:43:00.078 --> 00:43:02.147
He cannot come yet.

709
00:43:02.180 --> 00:43:05.350
Lina. fetch the midwives.

710
00:43:05.583 --> 00:43:07.352
It is too late.

711
00:43:07.585 --> 00:43:09.154
Catherine. look at me.

712
00:43:10.722 --> 00:43:13.058
We can do this together.

713
00:43:37.682 --> 00:43:40.785
Your Grace.
General Howard writes.

714
00:43:40.819 --> 00:43:44.022
Your sister's husband. Angus.
has betrayed her.

715
00:43:44.055 --> 00:43:45.299
Her heirs have both been seized.

716
00:43:45.323 --> 00:43:48.159
and she and Howard
are riding down to London.

717
00:43:48.193 --> 00:43:49.928
I said sending Howard
was a stupid bloody...

718
00:43:49.961 --> 00:43:53.932
No. no. Your Grace undoubtedly
made the right decision

719
00:43:53.965 --> 00:43:55.800
in sending him.

720
00:43:57.168 --> 00:43:59.037
Well. perhaps she's
learned her lesson now.

721
00:44:04.242 --> 00:44:05.243
Mm.

722
00:44:06.845 --> 00:44:10.248
Stafford. your sister
just pounced on Compton.

723
00:44:18.790 --> 00:44:21.259
Your Grace.
your child is coming early.

724
00:44:21.292 --> 00:44:23.361
- Lina is with her.
- I will go.

725
00:44:24.729 --> 00:44:26.831
The hour comes. Your Grace.

726
00:44:26.865 --> 00:44:30.001
The future of your kingdom
is fastened on this moment.

727
00:44:30.035 --> 00:44:32.103
I pray that the queen
will serve you.

728
00:44:32.137 --> 00:44:33.872
Congratulations. Henry.

729
00:44:33.905 --> 00:44:35.407
He comes.

730
00:44:36.708 --> 00:44:38.977
Come. Bessie. help me with this.

731
00:44:40.678 --> 00:44:42.147
Will he die?

732
00:44:42.180 --> 00:44:44.349
He will die if he comes
this early. won't he. Lina?

733
00:44:44.382 --> 00:44:48.019
Highness. God sends him
to you when he will.

734
00:44:49.854 --> 00:44:51.723
But you must push now.

735
00:44:51.756 --> 00:44:53.058
Push.

736
00:44:53.091 --> 00:44:55.060
We are with you. Catherine.

737
00:44:55.093 --> 00:44:57.062
Push.

738
00:45:01.132 --> 00:45:02.777
<i>Perhaps you'll
name him after me.</i>

739
00:45:02.801 --> 00:45:05.103
Prince Charles.

740
00:45:05.136 --> 00:45:07.839
- Has a ring to it.
- No. it's Henry.

741
00:45:07.872 --> 00:45:10.975
His name is Henry.
just like the first.

742
00:45:12.377 --> 00:45:14.379
Catherine. he is coming.

743
00:45:14.412 --> 00:45:16.147
He's nearly there.

744
00:45:17.816 --> 00:45:20.118
One big push.

745
00:45:32.130 --> 00:45:33.898
He's here.

746
00:45:35.800 --> 00:45:38.069
Our baby.

747
00:45:40.305 --> 00:45:42.073
Our new Prince Henry.

748
00:45:45.443 --> 00:45:47.078
Give him to me.

749
00:45:47.979 --> 00:45:49.280
Give... give him to me.

750
00:45:49.314 --> 00:45:51.182
Her.

751
00:45:52.450 --> 00:45:54.152
It's a girl. Catherine.

752
00:45:57.222 --> 00:45:58.857
It's a girl.

753
00:45:58.890 --> 00:46:01.926
Oh. no.

754
00:46:01.960 --> 00:46:04.963
No. no. No. no. no. no. no.

755
00:46:04.996 --> 00:46:07.265
It can't be. It can't be.
It can't be.

756
00:46:07.298 --> 00:46:09.033
How is my son?

757
00:46:11.236 --> 00:46:13.204
Tell me I have a healthy boy.

758
00:46:20.278 --> 00:46:22.280
Highness...

759
00:46:24.382 --> 00:46:25.850
The...

760
00:46:29.320 --> 00:46:32.891
...the... the baby is...
Is healthy.

761
00:46:34.159 --> 00:46:36.261
- Congratulations. Your Grace.
- Great job.

762
00:46:36.294 --> 00:46:39.998
She... is healthy.

763
00:46:42.233 --> 00:46:44.235
It is a girl.

764
00:46:44.269 --> 00:46:45.970
Will you hold her?

765
00:46:56.181 --> 00:46:57.949
She's crying for you.

766
00:46:59.083 --> 00:47:00.485
She needs her mother.

767
00:47:57.575 --> 00:47:59.244
Thank you for your efforts.

768
00:48:15.093 --> 00:48:17.061
<i>To His Most Christian Highness.</i>

769
00:48:17.095 --> 00:48:20.298
<i>Louis of France.</i>

770
00:48:20.331 --> 00:48:22.634
<i>England requests
that the duke of Albany</i>

771
00:48:22.667 --> 00:48:25.103
<i>return to Scotland
without delay.</i>

772
00:48:26.437 --> 00:48:29.140
<i>The Stewart heirs.
King Henry's nephews.</i>

773
00:48:29.173 --> 00:48:31.409
<i>have been abducted
by the Scottish clans.</i>

774
00:48:31.442 --> 00:48:32.610
<i>and Dowager Queen Margaret</i>

775
00:48:32.644 --> 00:48:36.247
<i>had to flee to England
for her life.</i>

776
00:48:36.281 --> 00:48:39.917
<i>Albany must take control
of Scotland.</i>

777
00:48:39.951 --> 00:48:41.986
<i>or there will be war.</i>

778
00:48:53.631 --> 00:48:56.934
Princess Mary likes
the gardens. Highness.

779
00:48:58.703 --> 00:49:00.972
Lina. this matter
of Anne Hastings.

780
00:49:02.106 --> 00:49:04.175
It seems it was Henry's groom.
Sir William.

781
00:49:04.208 --> 00:49:06.110
who was bedding her.
not my husband.

782
00:49:07.445 --> 00:49:09.347
I am glad to hear it. Highness.

783
00:49:10.448 --> 00:49:12.984
Well. shame on you
for listening to such gossip.

784
00:49:14.118 --> 00:49:16.163
Perhaps next time. you'll
think twice before you hurt me

785
00:49:16.187 --> 00:49:17.422
with such wicked lies

786
00:49:17.455 --> 00:49:19.257
and malign the king's good name.

787
00:49:20.558 --> 00:49:23.428
And now. because I questioned
Henry's loyalty. he is angry.

788
00:49:25.029 --> 00:49:26.631
And he will not come
to see me...

789
00:49:27.598 --> 00:49:29.200
...or his daughter.

790
00:49:30.234 --> 00:49:32.236
All he does is plan with Wolsey.

791
00:49:35.139 --> 00:49:37.642
I am sorry. Highness.

792
00:49:37.675 --> 00:49:39.644
Forgive me.

793
00:49:41.679 --> 00:49:43.147
Go home.

794
00:49:44.215 --> 00:49:46.417
I do not wish
to have you here today.

795
00:49:48.553 --> 00:49:50.221
Bessie will tend to me.

796
00:50:07.572 --> 00:50:10.108
- It's from Scotland.
- Give it to me.

797
00:50:10.141 --> 00:50:12.710
Compton. it is from Scotland.

798
00:50:12.744 --> 00:50:14.512
Have you forgotten
who the lady is?

799
00:50:15.713 --> 00:50:18.249
Howard. thank you.

800
00:50:18.282 --> 00:50:20.151
For everything.

801
00:50:21.119 --> 00:50:22.487
Go on. Go on.

802
00:50:26.357 --> 00:50:28.626
Children are
the heritage of the Lord.

803
00:50:28.659 --> 00:50:30.328
the fruit of the womb.

804
00:50:32.296 --> 00:50:34.432
Do not stand on my account.
dear brother.

805
00:50:34.465 --> 00:50:37.268
I do not; I've had my fill
of useless girls.

806
00:50:40.605 --> 00:50:41.739
You look old.

807
00:50:41.773 --> 00:50:43.608
You're getting fat.

808
00:50:44.375 --> 00:50:48.246
And I have had my sons
ripped out of my arms.

809
00:50:49.147 --> 00:50:52.283
You couldn't even
send me an army. brother.

810
00:50:52.316 --> 00:50:53.794
You're fortunate
I sent anyone at all. Meg.

811
00:50:53.818 --> 00:50:55.620
Sent someone. Yes. you did.

812
00:50:55.653 --> 00:50:57.822
You sent the duke of Albany

813
00:50:58.055 --> 00:51:00.491
to rule my country
and raise my children.

814
00:51:00.525 --> 00:51:02.393
Albany? He's in France...

815
00:51:02.427 --> 00:51:04.061
Uh. Your Grace.

816
00:51:05.797 --> 00:51:07.808
I took the liberty of summoning
the duke of Albany back

817
00:51:07.832 --> 00:51:09.333
on your behalf.

818
00:51:10.368 --> 00:51:12.637
Forgive me.

819
00:51:12.670 --> 00:51:16.307
Wolsey. are you
king of England now?

820
00:51:16.340 --> 00:51:19.577
Oh. so you have lost
your country too.

821
00:51:19.610 --> 00:51:21.646
to a butcher's boy from Ipswich.

822
00:51:21.679 --> 00:51:23.514
Wolsey has forgotten
I instructed him

823
00:51:23.548 --> 00:51:25.349
to write to France.

824
00:51:25.383 --> 00:51:27.852
Uh. of course.
Of course. Your Grace.

825
00:51:28.085 --> 00:51:30.521
Scotland must be stable
for our Tudor heirs

826
00:51:30.555 --> 00:51:32.457
to rule it
when they come of age.

827
00:51:32.490 --> 00:51:33.825
Albany will keep it so.

828
00:51:34.759 --> 00:51:38.763
Oh. to be a man and slap
each other's backs all day

829
00:51:38.796 --> 00:51:42.099
and sing of your own
good fortune.

830
00:51:42.133 --> 00:51:43.401
Where is Catherine?

831
00:51:43.434 --> 00:51:45.837
I will speak with someone
who sees sense.

832
00:51:53.344 --> 00:51:56.214
Of course I want the king
to have an heir.

833
00:51:56.247 --> 00:51:59.350
but there are many benefits
to daughters.

834
00:51:59.383 --> 00:52:02.520
I see in mine
all the flowers of England.

835
00:52:07.792 --> 00:52:09.861
Your Grace.

836
00:52:09.894 --> 00:52:11.696
I wish to ask you to release me

837
00:52:11.729 --> 00:52:13.865
from my betrothal
to Sir William Compton.

838
00:52:13.898 --> 00:52:16.734
Your Grace. you have
shown me great kindness.

839
00:52:16.767 --> 00:52:18.903
restoring my lands and titles.

840
00:52:19.136 --> 00:52:21.239
And you have made a fine match
for my daughter Ursula

841
00:52:21.272 --> 00:52:22.406
with Henry Stafford.

842
00:52:22.440 --> 00:52:24.175
I am grateful.

843
00:52:25.643 --> 00:52:27.278
But Sir William
kissed another woman.

844
00:52:27.311 --> 00:52:29.547
a married one at that.

845
00:52:29.580 --> 00:52:32.149
My honor would not stand for it.

846
00:52:32.850 --> 00:52:34.886
So I must refuse him.

847
00:52:47.565 --> 00:52:49.667
How convenient for you.
Lady Aunt...

848
00:52:50.835 --> 00:52:53.571
...when you were determined
not to do my bidding anyway.

849
00:52:56.407 --> 00:52:57.942
Go.

850
00:52:59.577 --> 00:53:01.512
You're released.

851
00:53:01.546 --> 00:53:03.714
Thank you. Your Grace.

852
00:53:08.386 --> 00:53:10.254
Lady Pole.

853
00:53:13.257 --> 00:53:15.560
I did your bidding.

854
00:53:15.593 --> 00:53:18.629
and I hope that I have
won your favor.

855
00:53:18.663 --> 00:53:20.565
I'm sorry. Sir William.

856
00:53:20.598 --> 00:53:24.502
but the king has withdrawn
his consent for us to marry.

857
00:53:28.906 --> 00:53:32.276
Excuse me.

858
00:53:35.279 --> 00:53:37.281
Lady Pole.

859
00:53:37.315 --> 00:53:39.517
Deftly played.

860
00:53:39.550 --> 00:53:41.452
I had no choice.

861
00:53:41.485 --> 00:53:43.254
I will not sacrifice myself.

862
00:53:43.287 --> 00:53:45.556
Oh. you do not need to justify
your character to me.

863
00:53:45.590 --> 00:53:47.658
You have always been
a faithful servant of God.

864
00:53:48.993 --> 00:53:51.629
I do have some news that may
be of use to you. though.

865
00:53:52.496 --> 00:53:54.632
It seems that all the stories

866
00:53:54.665 --> 00:53:58.002
about Anne Hastings
and our king were concocted

867
00:53:58.235 --> 00:54:00.838
by our great Archbishop Wolsey.

868
00:54:00.871 --> 00:54:02.473
Well. that is not a revelation.

869
00:54:02.506 --> 00:54:03.975
No. Indeed.

870
00:54:04.008 --> 00:54:07.011
But whilst Anne Hastings
was wrongly named.

871
00:54:07.244 --> 00:54:11.015
it seems that the king
does have a lover.

872
00:54:11.248 --> 00:54:12.683
Excuse me.

873
00:54:18.522 --> 00:54:20.524
My time at court has ended.

874
00:54:20.558 --> 00:54:24.929
The king has suggested
that I tend to my estate.

875
00:54:24.962 --> 00:54:26.897
and I gladly accept.

876
00:54:26.931 --> 00:54:28.966
You're being punished.

877
00:54:30.301 --> 00:54:32.536
You saved us from the Scots
at Flodden. yet...

878
00:54:32.570 --> 00:54:33.904
We both did that.

879
00:54:35.439 --> 00:54:39.810
If I had had a hundred men
with a heart like yours...

880
00:54:41.445 --> 00:54:43.014
...I could have conquered
the world.

881
00:54:45.516 --> 00:54:47.551
Just like
Alexander the fucking Great.

882
00:54:51.389 --> 00:54:54.725
Will you please stop cursing?

883
00:54:54.759 --> 00:54:57.361
Forgive me.

884
00:54:57.395 --> 00:54:59.330
I don't know when I'm doing it.

885
00:55:12.043 --> 00:55:14.045
- Your Grace.
- General Howard.

886
00:55:15.012 --> 00:55:17.481
They make me sick.
the pair of them.

887
00:55:18.582 --> 00:55:20.951
Wolsey and my brother.

888
00:55:20.985 --> 00:55:24.755
My poor boys will be terrified.
thinking I've abandoned them.

889
00:55:24.789 --> 00:55:28.426
Your Grace. I will take
her swaddling to the laundry.

890
00:55:34.598 --> 00:55:38.436
You must tell Henry to help me.

891
00:55:38.469 --> 00:55:40.104
Make clear to Albany

892
00:55:40.337 --> 00:55:42.406
that they must let me
raise my boys

893
00:55:42.440 --> 00:55:43.674
and be their regent.

894
00:55:43.708 --> 00:55:45.376
It will not work. Meg.

895
00:55:47.812 --> 00:55:49.547
We have all failed.

896
00:55:51.048 --> 00:55:52.950
Mary's trapped in France.

897
00:55:52.983 --> 00:55:55.419
married to a man
she wishes dead.

898
00:55:56.787 --> 00:55:59.457
Albany has your kingdom
for himself.

899
00:55:59.490 --> 00:56:00.691
I...

900
00:56:02.126 --> 00:56:05.396
You have given birth

901
00:56:05.429 --> 00:56:07.565
to a beautiful. healthy baby.

902
00:56:07.598 --> 00:56:09.700
A girl.

903
00:56:09.734 --> 00:56:11.402
What use is that?

904
00:56:12.536 --> 00:56:14.772
He thinks
that I have failed him.

905
00:56:16.874 --> 00:56:18.442
Look.

906
00:56:23.013 --> 00:56:25.883
Catherine. she's so beautiful.

907
00:56:27.551 --> 00:56:29.120
Look at her little face.

908
00:56:31.155 --> 00:56:33.491
Won't you take her?

909
00:56:36.594 --> 00:56:38.662
Bessie has forgotten this.

910
00:57:16.066 --> 00:57:19.069
